Title:View Modes
Crumbs:%ROOT%, Engine, Engine/UI/LevelEditor/Modes/MeshPaintMode/VertexColor
Description:A look at the different view modes available in Mesh Paint Mode.
Version: 4.9

[EXCERPT:Intro]
Mesh Paint Mode includes a variety of different view modes to aid in visualizing how vertex color is being applied to your meshes within the viewport. The view can display just the vertex colors, or can selectively view individual channels (red, green, blue, and alpha).
[/EXCERPT:Intro]

![](ViewModes.png)

|**Option** |**Description**|
| --- | --- |
|**Off**|Restores default editor view mode.|
|**RGB**|Displays Static Meshes unlit with only RGB vertex colors.|
|*R*|Displays Static Meshes unlit with only red vertex color.|
|*G*|Displays Static Meshes unlit with only green vertex color.|
|*B*|Displays Static Meshes unlit with only blue vertex color.|
|*A*|Displays Static Meshes unlit with only vertex alpha.|


![](ViewModes_Demo.png)
